               <msContents>
                  <summary>Anaphora of Our Lady Mary attributed to Cyriacus of Bǝhǝnsa, Qǝddase Maryam Gwäs’a, ቅዳሴ፡ ማርያም፡; Canticle of the Flower, Maḫletä Ṣǝge, ማሕሌተ፡ ጽጌ፡</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1"><locus from="1r" to="27r" facs="003">Fols 1r–27r</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1099Anapho">ʾAkkʷateta qʷǝrbān
                                                  za-qǝddus Hǝryāqos za-hagara Bǝhnǝsā</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ‘ǝz</textLang>
                  <note>This version differentiates the actions of the members of the Godhead, for example, <foreign xml:lang="gez">አብ፡ ይሄሊ፡ ወልድ፡ ይትናገር፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ይሠምር፡ <gap reason="omitted"/></foreign> (<locus target="#11v">fol. 11v</locus>)</note>
                </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2"><locus from="27r" to="66r" facs="029">Fols 27r–66r</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1834Mahlet">Māḫleta ṣǝge</title>
                  <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ‘ǝz</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
